## Slide 3 — Data Flow: Ingest to Memory

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Chan as Channel / UI
    participant GW as Gateway
    participant NATS as NATS
    participant Pipe as Pipeline (40 agents)
    participant LLM as Ollama / Gemini
    participant API as API
    participant DB as Supabase

    Chan->>GW: Webhook / upload
    GW->>API: Store raw data
    API->>DB: data_<ULID> created
    GW->>NATS: Publish UniversalEnvelope

    NATS->>Pipe: Pull consumer delivers
    Pipe->>Pipe: 6-layer classification
    Pipe->>LLM: Analyse (typed agent)
    LLM-->>Pipe: JSON: summary, entities, keywords
    Pipe->>API: Create viewpoint
    Pipe->>API: Auto-tag (category, entity, keyword)
    Pipe->>API: Generate embedding (pgvector)
    Pipe->>API: Batch create graph entities
```

**Key:** Raw data is stored before AI processing starts. Pipeline failures never lose data.

---

## Slide 4 — AI Pipeline: 40 Agents, 6-Layer Classification

### How data gets classified

No LLM needed for routing in most cases — 6 deterministic layers run first:

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    Data["Inbound Data"] --> L1["1. Channel message\ndetection"]
    L1 -->|miss| L2["2. Source type\nfield"]
    L2 -->|miss| L3["3. Explicit\ndata_type"]
    L3 -->|miss| L4["4. Payload field\nheuristic"]
    L4 -->|miss| L5["5. MIME\nregistry"]
    L5 -->|miss| L6["6. URL extension\nsniff"]
    L6 -->|miss| LLM["LLM Classifier\ngemma3:4b"]

    L1 & L2 & L3 & L4 & L5 & L6 & LLM -->|matched| Agent["Typed Sub-Agent"]
```

### 40+ specialized agents

| Category | Agent Types |
|----------|------------|
| **Documents** | PDF, Word, Excel, PowerPoint, HTML, Markdown, plain text |
| **Media** | Image, video (URL + stream), audio (URL + stream), image batch |
| **Communications** | Chat message, email, web page, calendar, RSS/Atom |
| **Structured** | CSV, JSON, XML, YAML |
| **Code** | Source code, log files, log streams |
| **Binary** | Archives, medical imaging (DICOM), time series |
| **Spatial** | LiDAR, geospatial (GeoJSON/KML/GPX), 3D models |
| **Sensor/IoT** | GPS, biometric, weather, industrial telemetry |
| **Scientific** | HDF5, NetCDF, FITS datasets |

### Tiered model routing

| Tier | Model | Used For |
|------|-------|----------|
| Small | gemma3:4b | Classification, simple structured data (JSON, CSV, XML) |
| Medium | gemma3:12b | Documents, code, communications |
| Large | gemma3:27b | Complex PDFs, Office docs, medical |
| Multimodal | Qwen3-VL | Images, video with visual content |
| Omni | Qwen3.5 | Audio, video with narration |
| Fallback | Gemini | When self-hosted models fail |

