## Slide 5 — Knowledge Graph

### Automatic entity extraction into Postgres

The AI pipeline extracts typed entities and relationships from every piece of data — no manual setup.

```mermaid
erDiagram
    mem_dog_entities {
        text entity_id PK
        text entity_type
        text entity_name
        text canonical_form
        float confidence
        jsonb metadata
    }
    mem_dog_relationships {
        text rel_id PK
        text source_entity_id FK
        text target_entity_id FK
        text rel_type
        float strength
    }
    mem_dog_entity_data_mapping {
        text mapping_id PK
        text entity_id FK
        text data_id
    }

    mem_dog_entities ||--o{ mem_dog_relationships : "source/target"
    mem_dog_entities ||--o{ mem_dog_entity_data_mapping : "appears in"
```

**Entity types:** person, organization, product, location, date, url, concept, event

**Entity-aware RAG:** When you ask a question, the chat endpoint:
1. Runs standard pgvector similarity search
2. Matches entity names from your query against the graph
3. Adds "Known entities" context to the LLM system prompt
4. Result: better answers when queries reference specific people, orgs, or concepts

---

## Slide 6 — Memory System

### 10 types, 4 categories, built-in expiry

| Type | Category | Default TTL | Purpose |
|------|----------|-------------|---------|
| conversation | conversation | 1 hour | Multi-turn dialogue |
| timeline | session | 7 days | Chronological activity log |
| session | session | 24 hours | Bounded interaction |
| tracing | session | 3 days | OTel trace spans |
| user | user | never | User profile facts |
| factual | user | never | Verified facts |
| episodic | user | temporary | Event memories |
| semantic | user | never | Conceptual knowledge |
| organizational | organizational | never | Org-level knowledge |
| custom | user | varies | User-defined |

**Access levels:** private (default), shared, public, restricted — with `shared_with` user list

**Memory compression:** LLM-powered summarization compresses verbose memories into structured summaries with key facts, entities, timeline, and action items. Auto-triggers at configurable thresholds (default: 50 items).

```python
m.compress("mem_conv_xyz", archive_originals=True)
# → {"summary_data_id": "data_...", "original_count": 47, "summary_length": 1823}
```

---

## Slide 7 — RAG Chat with Citations

### Conversational search across all stored data

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    Q["User question"] --> EMB["Generate\nquery embedding"]
    EMB --> SIM["pgvector\nsimilarity search"]
    SIM --> ENT["Entity-aware\nboost"]
    ENT --> CTX["Build numbered\ncontext"]
    CTX --> LLM["LLM with\nsystem prompt"]
    LLM --> ANS["Answer with\n[1] [2] citations"]
```

4 query modes:

| Endpoint | Use Case |
|----------|----------|
| `POST /ai/query` | Simple RAG query |
| `POST /ai/query/timeline` | Timeline-scoped query |
| `POST /ai/query/semantic` | Vector similarity search |
| `POST /ai/query/chat` | Conversational RAG with citations + history |

